My current suspicion

The key thing is that on June 12:

etcd -> disable
postgres -> disable
rabbit -> disable
sysinv -> disable

all happened together.

That is usually triggered by one of:

1. Host lock


2. Controller swact


3. Maintenance operation


4. Administrative disable


5. Reboot sequence



It is much less likely to be an etcd failure, because etcd was cleanly transitioned:

enabled-active -> disabling -> disabled

instead of crashing.

The output of:

sed -n '8550,8625p' /var/log/sm-service.log

should reveal exactly what event caused SM to start shutting everything down.
